I think what you want here is the following in the DAO:
@query("UPDATE tile_source SET reference_count=:newCount WHERE id = :id")
void updateReferenceCount(String id, int newCount);
You probably could also do the increment directly in SQL, but that might be overkill here.
Note that we've been following the convention that the table or entity is named after what each row describes, in this case "tile_source" instead of "tile_sources'.

